<div style="color:#0000FF">
Definition and Usage <br /> <br />
The div tag defines a division or a section in an HTML document. <br/>
The div tag is used to group block-elements to format them with CSS. <br/>
</div>

<br/>

<div>Lorem ipsum</div>
<div>Lorem ipsum</div>
<div>Lorem ipsum</div>
<div>Lorem ipsum</div>

<hr>

<div style="color:red">
Definition and Usage <br/> <br/>
The span tag is used to group inline-elements in a document. <br/>
The span tag provides no visual change by itself. <br/>
The span tag provides a way to add a hook to a part of a text or a part of a document. <br/>
</div> 

<br/> 

<span>Lorem ipsum</span>
<span>Lorem ipsum</span>
<span>Lorem ipsum</span>
<span>Lorem ipsum</span>

